dismissalText.commentary: Sese Bau lbw b Anshuman Rath 44 (57b 2x4 2x6) SR: 77.19

dismissalComment.html: Rath gets his third wicket, this was on a flatter length which was pitched outside off and sliding in with the angle. Bau gets half forward and tries to drive, playing inside the line. Ball went past the outside edge and hits the back pad.

headshotImage.longCaption: Anshuman Rath player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Lega Siaka player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Lega Siaka player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Rath gets his first wicket, this was tossed up outside off from round the wicket, this ball kept straight. Siaka gets down and tries to slog across the line. He ends up skying it towards the cover region off the top edge, Hayat back tracks and collects it.

headshotImage.caption: Vani Vagi Morea player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Vani Vagi Morea player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Morea once again dances down the track and tries to attack. Rath saw him coming and pushes this quicker and follows his legs. Morea plays across the line and ball turns away too after pitching around the leg stump, through the bat pad gap and shatters the stumps..

headshotImage.caption: Sese Bau player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sese Bau player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Rath gets his third wicket, this was on a flatter length which was pitched outside off and sliding in with the angle. Bau gets half forward and tries to drive, playing inside the line. Ball went past the outside edge and hits the back pad.

headshotImage.caption: Dogodo Bau player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dogodo Bau player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: and Nadeem breaks the partnership. He comes round the wicket and bowls a flighted one around middle and leg. This ball held the deck and grips. Dogodo was early onto his shot as he tries to flick that through the leg side, gets a leading edge which lobs back to the bowler.

dismissalText.commentary: Chad Soper c †Carter b Aizaz Khan 16 (30b 1x4 0x6) SR: 53.33

dismissalComment.html: back of a length and outside off. Soper was standing outside the leg stump and tries to cut it. Edges it back to the keeper. There was no real attempt from him to get closer to the line, plays away from the body and paid the price. Also this ball bounces touch extra with good pace.

commentTextItems.html: that's it, Rath gets to his fifty too with this boundary, fuller length around off as he slogs it through midwicket

commentPostTextItems.html: Hong Kong won by 7 wickets (D/L method) and sealed the series 2-1. Anshuman Rath named Man of the Match and Babar Hayat is Man of the Series .. That's all from this match, thanks for joining us. Good night.

commentTextItems.html: on a length but way outside off
touch short at off stump, slogs across the line, only an inside edge to the pad
short of a length outside off, punches into cover point
length ball and a bit of inward movement, Babar smashes that straight over the mid-on region

3:25 pm: Players are off the field and covers are coming on..

milestones.description: Tony Ura and Vani Morea's 56-run partnership is PNG's highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 17 between Tony Ura and Vani Morea
Sese Bau and Dogodo Bau's 45-run partnership is PNG's highest for the 5th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 34 between Mahuru Dai and Vani Morea
Mahuru Dai and Chad Soper's 57-run partnership is PNG's highest for the 7th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 36 between Jack Vare and Charles Amini
Mahuru Dai and Hiri Hiri's 43-run partnership is PNG's highest for the 8th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 28 between Chris Amini and Vani Morea
Babar Hayat has broken the record for most sixes (14) in ODIs for HKG, going past Nizakat Khan's 11
Babar Hayat has broken the record for most ODIs (5) as captain for HKG, going past Atkinson
Assad Vala has broken the record for most ODIs (3) as captain for PNG, going past Chris Amini
Mahuru Dai has broken the record for most sixes in an innings (4) in ODIs for PNG, going past Lega Siaka's 2
Mahuru Dai has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (5) for PNG, going past Vani Morea
